@node "English"
                                                   Malaga (Spain) 19-7-06


This animation is the product of sleepless nights and work trying to solve
problem by problem.

the  first test animation started in (10/12/95) and the last 'frame-insert'
finished in (9/1/96).

About 45megs of test animations were generated before the final render.

This animation was about to be errased by some 'validation errors' mainly
for mainly for interuptions in the power supply.

It's very strange, when WB get 'invalidated' the system try to emulate
'Windows 95' and load with equal speed than WIN95!! GREAT! ;-)

  @{u} AND THEY TOLD THE AMIGA NEVER COULD  RUN WIN95!! @{uu}

 @{"Making Of... 'A kind Of Magic'"  link MAKING}

@endnode

@node "MAKING"

I used LightWave 3.5 from Newtek to make the whole animation.

1º I created every object in lw's 'Modeller'.

2º I Made separeted scenes for every character, then I inserted it in a
   scene that had the objects backgrounds.

3º I rendered every frames at 320*240 pixels in 24bits, then I converted
   then to HAM8 using Dpaint5 with one palette per frame, 'Rend24' did not
   work with this resolution.Then I mounted (by hand) every frames in small
   anims (about 1mg) in DpaintV, because I have not enought memory.

4º Using 'Anim WorkShop' and 'ADPRO' I scaled every frame to 220*116 HAM8,
   in 320*240 the anim could have took about 11 megs.

5º I also used 'MainActor' to add the final anims to the first anim, every
   anim took 1 meg.

Every frame took about 6 minutes and 20 seconds to render, im 'realistisc
mode' with 'shadows' enable, the flare frames took about 11 minutes each.
